{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.34",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 34,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 34",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 34 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:1",
      "text": "Then Elihu said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:2",
      "text": "“Hear my words, you wise men, and give ear to me, you who know;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:3",
      "text": "for the ear tests words as the palate tastes food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:4",
      "text": "Let us choose what is right; let us determine among ourselves what is good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:5",
      "text": "For Job has said, ‘I am innocent, and God has taken away my right;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:6",
      "text": "in spite of my right I am counted a liar; my wound is incurable, though I am without transgression.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:7",
      "text": "What man is like Job, who drinks up scoffing like water,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:8",
      "text": "who goes in company with evildoers and walks with wicked men?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:9",
      "text": "For he has said, ‘It profits a man nothing that he should take delight in God.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:10",
      "text": "“Therefore, hear me, you men of understanding, far be it from God that he should do wickedness, and from the Almighty that he should do wrong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:11",
      "text": "For according to the work of a man he will requite him, and according to his ways he will make it befall him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:12",
      "text": "Of a truth, God will not do wickedly, and the Almighty will not pervert justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:13",
      "text": "Who gave him charge over the earth and who laid on him the whole world?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:14",
      "text": "If he should take back his spirit to himself, and gather to himself his breath,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:15",
      "text": "all flesh would perish together, and man would return to dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:16",
      "text": "“If you have understanding, hear this; listen to what I say.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:17",
      "text": "Shall one who hates justice govern? Will you condemn him who is righteous and mighty,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:18",
      "text": "who says to a king, ‘Worthless one,’ and to nobles, ‘Wicked man’;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:19",
      "text": "who shows no partiality to princes, nor regards the rich more than the poor, for they are all the work of his hands?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:20",
      "text": "In a moment they die; at midnight the people are shaken and pass away, and the mighty are taken away by no human hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:21",
      "text": "“For his eyes are upon the ways of a man, and he sees all his steps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:22",
      "text": "There is no gloom or deep darkness where evildoers may hide themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:23",
      "text": "For he has not appointed a time for any man to go before God in judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:24",
      "text": "He shatters the mighty without investigation, and sets others in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:25",
      "text": "Thus, knowing their works, he overturns them in the night, and they are crushed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:26",
      "text": "He strikes them for their wickedness in the sight of men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:27",
      "text": "because they turned aside from following him, and had no regard for any of his ways,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:28",
      "text": "so that they caused the cry of the poor to come to him, and he heard the cry of the afflicted—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:29",
      "text": "When he is quiet, who can condemn? When he hides his face, who can behold him, whether it be a nation or a man?—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:30",
      "text": "that a godless man should not reign, that he should not ensnare the people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:31",
      "text": "“For has any one said to God, ‘I have borne chastisement; I will not offend any more;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:32",
      "text": "teach me what I do not see; if I have done iniquity, I will do it no more’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:33",
      "text": "Will he then make requital to suit you, because you reject it? For you must choose, and not I; therefore declare what you know.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:34",
      "text": "Men of understanding will say to me, and the wise man who hears me will say:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:35",
      "text": "‘Job speaks without knowledge, his words are without insight.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:36",
      "text": "Would that Job were tried to the end, because he answers like wicked men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.34.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 34:37",
      "text": "For he adds rebellion to his sin; he claps his hands among us, and multiplies his words against God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
